18/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A large number of Bulgarian municipalities have shown interest in hosting US military bases, Foreign Minister Solomon Passy announced Friday (16 July). He said 35 letters of interest have been filed so far, adding that local communities see the possible bases as an opportunity for an economic boost. Washington has not yet made a decision on whether and when to establish the bases. (BTA, Sega - 16/07/04)
